<subSubSection id="C31665519534FF87798CF848FEB9FEC9" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="8BB336DA9534FF87798CF848FEB9FEC9" blockId="5.[151,1436,1948,2015]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,152,298]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89534FF84798CF848FEB9F855" bold="true" box="[151,315,1948,1974]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">
<typeStatus id="54B788789534FF84798CF848FF56F855" box="[151,212,1948,1974]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
† 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599534FF84784AF849FC83F854" authority="Kovalev 1990" authorityName="Kovalev" authorityYear="1990" box="[337,769,1949,1975]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesozoica">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89534FF84784AF849FDD0F855" box="[337,594,1949,1974]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Catotricha mesozoica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B2B9534FF847B42F849FC83F854" author="Kovalev, V." box="[601,769,1949,1975]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" pagination="123 - 177" refId="ref4269" refString="Kovalev, V. (1990) [Diptera.] In: Rasnitsyn, A. P. (Ed.), [Late Mesozoic Insects of Eastern Transbaikalia.] Nauka Press, Moscow, pp. 123 - 177. [In Russian.]" type="book chapter" year="1990">Kovalev 1990</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="B978EAC89534FF8479DDF810FEC4F83D" bold="true" box="[198,326,1988,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus differs from extant 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599534FF847BDAF811FCE0F83C" authorityName="Edwards" authorityYear="1938" box="[705,866,1989,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Catotrichinae">Catotrichinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599534FF847A74F811FC6CF83D" authorityName="Edwards. This" authorityYear="1938" box="[879,1006,1989,2014]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89534FF847A74F811FC6CF83D" box="[879,1006,1989,2014]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Catotricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599534FF847D31F811FB2BF83D" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" box="[1066,1193,1989,2014]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Trichotoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89534FF847D31F811FB2BF83D" box="[1066,1193,1989,2014]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="58">Trichotoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in the considerably shorter and broader wings and shorter legs. The ratio of wing length to width is 
<quantity id="4CF49B3F9537FF877D69FF4CFB3AFF51" box="[1138,1208,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.334" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" unit="in" value="2.1">2.1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877DD8FF4CFAE6FF52" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" box="[1219,1380,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Mesotrichoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877DD8FF4CFAE6FF52" box="[1219,1380,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Mesotrichoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<quantity id="4CF49B3F9537FF87798CFF14FE8CFF39" box="[151,270,192,218]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.239" metricValueMax="7.874" metricValueMin="6.604" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" unit="in" value="2.85" valueMax="3.1" valueMin="2.6">2.6–3.1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF87780DFF14FE4CFF39" box="[278,462,192,218]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF87780DFF14FE17FF3A" box="[278,405,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Catotricha</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
and 3.0– 
<quantity id="4CF49B3F9537FF877B27FF14FDFDFF39" box="[572,639,192,218]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.636" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" unit="in" value="3.4">3.4 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877B9CFF14FCBDFF39" box="[647,831,192,218]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Trichotoca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877B9CFF14FC84FF3A" box="[647,774,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Trichotoca</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
Mid legs (femora through tarsi) are slightly longer than the body in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877845FF3CFE7DFEE2" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" box="[350,511,232,257]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Mesotrichoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877845FF3CFE7DFEE2" box="[350,511,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Mesotrichoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 1.5 times as long as the body in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877AA2FF3CFBBAFEE2" authorityName="Edwards. This" authorityYear="1938" box="[953,1080,232,257]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877AA2FF3CFBBAFEE2" box="[953,1080,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Catotricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and twice as long as the body in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF8779AEFEC4FEB6FECA" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" box="[181,308,272,297]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Trichotoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF8779AEFEC4FEB6FECA" box="[181,308,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Trichotoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF7366529537FF87798CFBCCFD00FBB1" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5242009" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5242009" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5242009/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" startId="6.[151,255,1048,1072]" targetBox="[190,1399,364,1012]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8BB336DA9537FF87798CFBCCFD00FBB1" blockId="6.[151,1436,1048,1106]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF87798CFBCCFE9AFBD3" bold="true" box="[151,280,1048,1072]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">FIGURE 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877804FBCDFDE5FBCC" authority="(Jaschhof)" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[287,615,1048,1072]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Trichotoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fraterna">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877804FBCDFE72FBD3" box="[287,496,1049,1072]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Trichotoca fraterna</emphasis>
(Jaschhof)
</taxonomicName>
, various specimens. 
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877A58FBCCFC02FBD3" bold="true" box="[835,896,1048,1072]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">A–C:</emphasis>
Tegmen and ejaculatory apodeme. 
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877DE2FBCCFAB0FBD3" bold="true" box="[1273,1330,1048,1072]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">D–F:</emphasis>
Gonostylus. Specimens from Warra. Scale = 0.05 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C31665519537FF8779DDFB54FCB0F998" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB336DA9537FF8779DDFB54FF5CF9C8" blockId="6.[151,1436,1152,1659]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF8779DDFB54FED0FB79" bold="true" box="[198,338,1152,1178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Discussion.</emphasis>
Wing venation, antennal structure, and a remarkable overall resemblance give sufficient evidence for 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877817FB7DFE2FFB21" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" box="[268,429,1193,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Mesotrichoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877817FB7DFE2FFB21" box="[268,429,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Mesotrichoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being indeed a catotrichine (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B2B9537FF877A33FB7DFC50FB20" author="Kovalev, V." box="[808,978,1193,1219]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="123 - 177" refId="ref4269" refString="Kovalev, V. (1990) [Diptera.] In: Rasnitsyn, A. P. (Ed.), [Late Mesozoic Insects of Eastern Transbaikalia.] Nauka Press, Moscow, pp. 123 - 177. [In Russian.]" type="book chapter" year="1990">Kovalev 1990</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 136). Body proportions of the 
<specimenCount id="9D0AFD539537FF877C6AFB7DFE84FB08" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
preserved, though apparently in good shape, are the only characters available to compare 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF87798CFB2DFEBAFAF1" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,312,1273,1298]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Mesotrichoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF87798CFB2DFEBAFAF1" box="[151,312,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Mesotrichoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the other catotrichine genera. We assume that broad wings and relatively short legs are plesiomorphous character states. The relatively short flagellomere necks and stout nodes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877DB5FAF5FACDFAD9" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" box="[1198,1359,1313,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Mesotrichoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877DB5FAF5FACDFAD9" box="[1198,1359,1313,1338]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Mesotrichoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be apomorphous, but we cannot be sure whether or not these are artifacts. Clearly apomorphous features are not recognizable for 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF87788EFAA5FDB4FA69" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" box="[405,566,1393,1418]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Mesotrichoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF87788EFAA5FDB4FA69" box="[405,566,1393,1418]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Mesotrichoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which appears to be an extinct sister-group to the living catotrichines, (
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF8779BAFA4DFEA2FA51" authorityName="Edwards. This" authorityYear="1938" box="[161,288,1433,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF8779BAFA4DFEA2FA51" box="[161,288,1433,1458]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Catotricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF87782BFA4DFE2DFA51" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" box="[304,431,1433,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Trichotoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF87782BFA4DFE2DFA51" box="[304,431,1433,1458]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Trichotoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9D4B2B9537FF8778D1FA4DFD40FA50" author="Kovalev, V." box="[458,706,1433,1459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" pagination="123 - 177" refId="ref4269" refString="Kovalev, V. (1990) [Diptera.] In: Rasnitsyn, A. P. (Ed.), [Late Mesozoic Insects of Eastern Transbaikalia.] Nauka Press, Moscow, pp. 123 - 177. [In Russian.]" type="book chapter" year="1990">Kovalev (1990: 175)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that the generic classification of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877DFFFA4DFADCFA51" box="[1252,1374,1433,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesozoica">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877DFFFA4DFADCFA51" box="[1252,1374,1433,1458]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">mesozoica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF87798CFA15FE94FA39" authorityName="Edwards. This" authorityYear="1938" box="[151,278,1473,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF87798CFA15FE94FA39" box="[151,278,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Catotricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– something he himself questioned – rendered 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877A52FA15FC4AFA39" authorityName="Edwards. This" authorityYear="1938" box="[841,968,1473,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877A52FA15FC4AFA39" box="[841,968,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Catotricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
one of the oldest recent genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877C7DFA15FF44F9E0" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
. We do not see any indication for 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877B54FA3DFD4BF9E1" box="[591,713,1513,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesozoica">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877B54FA3DFD4BF9E1" box="[591,713,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">mesozoica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being a member of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877D3CFA3DFB24F9E1" authorityName="Edwards. This" authorityYear="1938" box="[1063,1190,1513,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877D3CFA3DFB24F9E1" box="[1063,1190,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Catotricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the narrowed here sense.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB336DA9537FF87798CF9EDFCB0F998" blockId="6.[151,1436,1152,1659]" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF87798CF9EDFE91F9B1" box="[151,275,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF877880F9EDFDBEF9B1" authorityName="Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2008" box="[411,572,1593,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Mesotrichoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877880F9EDFDBEF9B1" box="[411,572,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Mesotrichoca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed of 
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877BE1F9EDFCB4F9B1" box="[762,822,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">meso</emphasis>
-, from Mesozoic, and - 
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF877D53F9EDFB2BF9B1" box="[1096,1193,1593,1618]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">trichoca</emphasis>
, an abbreviated anagram of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0C4D599537FF8779E1F9B5FEFBF999" authorityName="Edwards. This" authorityYear="1938" box="[250,377,1633,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Catotricha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B978EAC89537FF8779E1F9B5FEFBF999" box="[250,377,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="59">Catotricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The gender of this noun is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
